{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a65417cc3fb48d66102", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "EM", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9b"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "648b5a3a0d9d0b909f7b6489", "title": "JEE Main 2017 (02 Apr)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "In the given circuit diagram, when the current reaches a steady-state in the circuit, the charge on the capacitor of capacitance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> will be:<br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/8f49c2e0-ad87-4bda-94f4-777793c628b7-image.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 182px;\" />", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "fm8JW", "text": "<math><mi>C</mi><mi>E</mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "WXT67", "text": "<math><mi>C</mi><mi>E</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "XLUfv", "text": "<math><mi>C</mi><mi>E</mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "VkEO0", "text": "<math><mi>C</mi><mi>E</mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>In steady state, current through capacitor will be zero, so current through <math><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> will be zero.</p><p>Hence, the net current flowing in the circuit will be,<br /><math><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br />The potential difference across the capacitor will be,<br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>I</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>E</mi><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore, charge on the capacitor plate will be,<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>E</mi><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ34817335", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfa